# Security Rules

- NEVER commit secrets, API keys, tokens, or passwords
- NEVER hardcode paths that vary between systems
- USB HID write paths must validate device identity before sending data
- All file writes must use safe paths within the project directory
- Capture backends must handle permission failures gracefully
- HID communication: validate response lengths and error codes before parsing
